name: II. “CERES, BACCHUS AND VENUS”
description:
2/4 from the “REVIVAL” collection.
REVIVAL is a NFT collection that was born with the purpose of reviving important portions of art history that were silenced and deteriorated by the passage of time.
An alchemical process that connects with spirits that left the earthly plane in past times.

Description of the piece:
Venus flanked by Bacchus and Ceres with their attributes, on the left and right of the composition, respectively. On the left, at the bottom, a winged child figure trying to reach the grapes held by Bacchus. Sine Cerere et Baccho Friget Venus (Without Ceres and Bacchus Venus Would Freeze).
- Saenredam, Jan Pieterszoon. 1615 - 1665.

AS ABOVE, SO BELOW.
